## Note  


Turning the front cam one graduation on the scale changes the caster angle about \(25^{\circ}\) and the camber about \(29^{\circ}\) . Turning the rear cam one graduation changes the caster angle about \(25^{\circ}\) and the camber about \(2^{\circ}\) .  


3. Adjust the camber and the toe-in.  


## Camber Adjustment  


## Caution  


Adjust the camber after adjusting the caster.  


1. Loosen the front and rear cam nuts. 
2. Turn the front and rear adjusting cam bolts the same amount in the opposite direction to provide the correct camber angle.  

